Using searchingforstrangeness
=============================

Copyright (C) searchingforstrangeness contributors.

This file describes normal use of the package after it has been checked out and
built inside a MicroBooNE ubana development area.  For installation and build
instructions, see INSTALL.  For a repository overview, see README.  For
dataset naming and SAM-definition notes, see scripts/README.md.


Conventions
-----------

The examples below assume:

  * you are running from the top of this repository;
  * the package has already been built in a working MRB area;
  * the MicroBooNE software environment is active;
  * your input files are art ROOT files from the expected reconstruction chain.

Several checked-in FHiCL files use relative paths such as "runtime" and
"scripts/inference_wrapper.sh".  Running from the repository top directory is
the simplest way to make those paths resolve as expected.


1. Prepare the runtime environment
----------------------------------

Complete the setup and build steps in INSTALL first.

For interactive work from this checkout, the usual sequence is:

     ./.container.sh
     source .setup.sh

If your shell is already in the correct MicroBooNE/MRB environment, sourcing
.setup.sh from the repository top directory is usually enough.  That helper
also sets up sam_web_client for the SAM-based workflows described below.


2. Choose a checked-in job configuration
----------------------------------------

The standard entry points are under job/.

job/run_nuselection.fcl
     Runs the neutrino-selection filter on MC-style input and writes the
     analysis TTree file nu_selection.root.

job/run_nuselection_data.fcl
     Runs the data/EXT version of the selection and writes
     nu_selection_data.root.

job/run_nuselection_noinference.fcl
     Runs the MC-style selection on input that already contains imageprod
     products, but skips loading inference products.  It writes
     nu_selection_noinference.root.

job/run_nuselection_data_noinference.fcl
     Runs the data/EXT selection on input that already contains imageprod
     products, but skips loading inference products.  It writes
     nu_selection_data_noinference.root.

job/run_imageprod.fcl
     Produces image::SparsePlaneImage objects for the selected slice and a
     full-detector companion collection, then writes the event file
     %ifb_%tc_imageprod.root.  The checked-in TFileService output is
     imageprod_hist.root.

job/run_inferenceprod.fcl
     Runs model inference on existing imageprod:CroppedWindow products and writes
     the event file %ifb_%tc_inference.root.  The checked-in TFileService
     output is inferenceprod_hist.root.

job/run_fullchain.fcl
     Runs image production, inference, and neutrino selection in one process.
     It writes %ifb_%tc_fullchain_nuselection.root and
     fullchain_nuselection_hist.root.

The development entry points are under dev/.

dev/image_dev.fcl
     Development chain for imaging, inference, and selection with event-weight
     analysis enabled.

dev/image_dev_cosmic.fcl
     Development chain for cosmic/data-style imaging and selection studies.

dev/run_stage_evtw_cv_dev.fcl through dev/run_stage_evtw_extragenie5_dev.fcl
     Local wrappers for the staged Run 1 FHC eventweight chain.  Run them in
     the same order as the staged XML when you want to reproduce the
     `*_evtw` substage sequence on a small local sample.  These wrappers use
     the NuMI old-flux reweighting chain.

dev/run_stage_image_dev.fcl
     Local wrapper for the staged image-production step.

dev/run_stage_infer_dev.fcl
     Local wrapper for the staged inference step.

dev/run_stage_sel_dev.fcl
     Local wrapper for the staged MC-style selection step.

dev/run_stage_sel_data_dev.fcl
     Local wrapper for the staged data/EXT-style selection step.

dev/run_stage_fullchain_dev.fcl
     Local wrapper for running the image, inference, and selection chain in
     one process while still using dev-local output names.

dev/amarantin_local_dev.fcl
     Local MC-style ntuple job for downstream amarantin testing.  It runs the
     eventweight and image stages in-process, writes the EventSelectionFilter
     and SubRun trees, limits the local sample to 100 events, keeps only 100
     GENIE and 100 PPFX universes, uses the NuMI old-flux reweighting chain,
     and leaves inference disabled until the checked-in model bundle is
     refreshed.

dev/run_numisystematicweights_rhc_extragenie1.fcl
     Standalone extra-GENIE RHC event-weight job writing
     %ifb_extragenie1_rhc.root.

dev/numi_fhc_run1_dev.xml
     Grid job template for the dev imaging and inference chain.


3. Run local jobs
-----------------

The most common command form is:

     lar -c <fhicl_file> -s <input.root>

Examples:

     lar -c job/run_nuselection.fcl -s reco_input.root

     lar -c job/run_nuselection_data.fcl -s data_input.root

     lar -c job/run_nuselection_noinference.fcl -s imageprod_output.root

     lar -c job/run_nuselection_data_noinference.fcl -s imageprod_output.root

     lar -c job/run_imageprod.fcl -s reco_input.root

     lar -c job/run_inferenceprod.fcl -s imageprod_output.root

     lar -c job/run_fullchain.fcl -s reco_input.root

Usage notes:

  * Use run_nuselection.fcl when you want flat analysis trees from MC-like
    input.
  * Use run_nuselection_data.fcl for data or EXT workflows.
  * Use the `*_noinference` selection jobs on input that contains
    `imageprod:CroppedWindow` and `imageprod:FullWindow` products when you do
    not want to run or depend on `inferenceprod`.
  * Use run_imageprod.fcl when you want persisted image products in the art
    event output.
  * Use run_inferenceprod.fcl only on input files that already contain the
    imageprod:CroppedWindow products expected by the InferenceProducer.
  * Use run_fullchain.fcl when starting from reconstructed input and you want
    the image, inference, and selection stages in one step.

For quick staged-workflow tests from this checkout, `.local.sh` now supports
either a SAM-backed mini-run or a direct local handoff between stages:

     SAM_DEF=prodgenie_numi_uboone_overlay_fhc_mcc9_run1_v28_v2_sample0 \
       ./.local.sh dev/run_stage_evtw_cv_dev.fcl 1

     ./.local.sh dev/run_stage_image_dev.fcl \
       /absolute/path/to/previous_stage.root

When you pass an integer as the second argument, `.local.sh` resolves that many
files from `SAM_DEF`.  When you pass a `.root` path as the second argument, it
uses that file directly.  Outputs are written under `local-output/` by default.
Histogram outputs are combined automatically; art event outputs are left as
per-file ROOT files and are also listed in a `*_events.list` manifest so they
can be fed into the next stage.

For a compact downstream amarantin input file, run the dedicated local ntuple
job on a single SAM file:

     SAM_DEF=prodgenie_numi_uboone_overlay_fhc_mcc9_run1_v28_v2_sample0 \
       ./.local.sh dev/amarantin_local_dev.fcl 1

That produces one combined TFileService ROOT file under `local-output/`.
Because `amarantin` consumes the EventSelectionFilter and SubRun trees, this
selection-ntuple output is the intended local-test surface rather than a full
art event file.

The inference jobs expect the checked-in runtime bundle under runtime/,
including runtime/models/mink_binary/checkpoint_step0010000.pt and the wrapper
script reached through the RuntimeBaseDir setting.

When you want to run the same network architecture with multiple checkpoints,
put the shared settings in ModelDefaults and vary only the per-model labels and
Checkpoint values:

     ModelDefaults: {
       Arch: "binary:device=cpu,seed=12345,thr=0.0,in_ch=3"
       WeightsDir: "models/mink_binary"
     }
     Models: [
       { Label: "mink_binary_step0010000" Checkpoint: "checkpoint_step0010000.pt" }
       { Label: "mink_binary_step0020000" Checkpoint: "checkpoint_step0020000.pt" }
     ]


4. Run over SAM definitions
---------------------------

For quick local tests, a common pattern is to resolve a few files from a SAM
definition and loop over them:

     files=$(samweb list-files defname:<sam_definition> | head -n 3)

     counter=1
     for file in $files; do
         filedir=$(samweb locate-file "$file" | grep -o '/pnfs/.*' | head -n 1)
         lar -c job/run_fullchain.fcl -s "${filedir}/${file}"
         mv fullchain_nuselection_hist.root "fullchain_${counter}.root"
         counter=$((counter + 1))
     done

     hadd -f combined_fullchain.root fullchain_*.root

If you need to prepare or inspect SAM definitions, use the helper scripts in
scripts/ and the top-level describe-definitions.sh helper:

     ./scripts/split_detvar_stride.sh <source_def> <training_def> <plotting_def>

     ./describe-definitions.sh

scripts/README.md records the canonical Run 1 FHC source definitions and the
legacy good-runs helper commands.  The checked-in XML workflows use the source
definitions directly.


5. Understand the outputs
-------------------------

The package writes two kinds of ROOT output.

art event files
     These are written by jobs such as run_imageprod.fcl, run_inferenceprod.fcl,
     run_fullchain.fcl, and the extra-GENIE weight job.  They contain event
     products such as image::SparsePlaneImage and inference products.

TFileService analysis files
     These are files such as nu_selection.root, nu_selection_data.root, and
     fullchain_nuselection_hist.root.  They contain TTrees and analysis
     branches intended for downstream plotting and ntuple-style analysis.

The checked-in branch and product layout is summarized here.  In particular:

  * EventSelectionFilter trees live in nu_selection.root,
    nu_selection_data.root, fullchain_nuselection_hist.root,
    imaging_dev.root, and imaging_dev_cosmic.root.
  * ImageProducer writes the neutrino-centered sparse planes to
    imageprod:CroppedWindow and the detector-wide sparse planes to
    imageprod:FullWindow.
  * The image-only and inference-only histogram files are mainly framework
    side outputs; the repo-defined payload for those workflows is in the art
    event file.


6. Submit grid jobs
-------------------

The repository includes five checked-in grid XML workflows:

  * xml/numi_fhc_run1.xml
    This keeps eventweight, image production, and selection in the same
    submitted stage as sequential substages.  For now it keeps only the first
    eventweight chunk (100 multisim universes), uses the NuMI old-flux
    reweighting chain, and skips inference until the checked-in models are
    updated.
  * xml/numi_fhc_run2a_campaign.xml
    This is the Run 2a FHC campaign template built from the Run 2a NuMI sample
    inventory in the internal note.  It uses one nominal beam sample, one dirt
    sample, one strangeness sample, and four good-run EXT partitions.  Its
    `numjobs` values are placeholders and should be replaced from `samweb`
    counts in a configured environment before submission.  Like the Run 1
    campaign XML, it currently keeps only the first eventweight chunk, uses the
    NuMI old-flux reweighting chain, and skips inference until the checked-in
    models are updated.
  * xml/numi_fhc_run1_staged.xml
    This currently splits the workflow into `*_evtw`, `*_image`, and `*_sel`
    stages.  Each `*_evtw` stage keeps only the first eventweight chunk, uses
    the NuMI old-flux reweighting chain, and each later stage consumes the
    checked output of the previous one.
    Dedicated `*_infer` stages are commented out until the checked-in models
    are updated.
  * xml/numi_fhc_run1_training.xml
    This is the training-oriented workflow.  It skips inference entirely, runs
    only the first eventweight chunk for MC, uses the NuMI old-flux
    reweighting chain, and uses the no-inference selection FHiCL wrappers.
  * xml/numi_fhc_run1_detvar_training.xml
    This is the stride-split detector-variation training workflow.  It targets
    the training definitions created by `scripts/split_detvar_stride.sh` and
    runs only `image -> sel` with the no-inference MC selection wrapper.

The repository also includes four source-samdef Reco2 campaign templates built
from the March 2022 NuMI dataset list plus the matching dedicated strangeness
overlay samples recorded in the internal note:

  * xml/numi_reco2_run1_fhc_campaign.xml
    Run 1 FHC source campaign using the official Reco2 beam, dirt, EXT, and
    beam-good data definitions together with the Run 1 FHC strangeness sample.
  * xml/numi_reco2_run2a_fhc_campaign.xml
    Run 2a FHC source campaign using the official Reco2 source definitions.
    It defaults to the clearly FHC-tagged beam definition and documents the
    duplicated `run2_numi_nu_overlay_pandora_unified_reco2_run2b_rhc_reco2`
    line from the March 2022 list as an ambiguity to review manually.
  * xml/numi_reco2_run2b_rhc_campaign.xml
    Run 2b RHC source campaign using the regenerated RHC beam definition, the
    Run 2 RHC dirt and strangeness samples, plus the listed EXT and data defs.
  * xml/numi_reco2_run3b_rhc_campaign.xml
    Run 3b RHC source campaign using the four official beam shards, the two
    dirt shards, the Run 3 RHC strangeness sample, and the listed EXT/data
    definitions.

These Reco2 source templates keep only the first eventweight chunk, disable
inference until the checked-in models are updated, and leave all `numjobs`
values as placeholders that should be replaced with
`samweb count-files defname:<...>` results before submission.

Before submitting, review the XML entities near the top of the file you plan
to use.  They hard-code values such as:

  * the release tag;
  * the user name;
  * tarball and output PNFS locations;
  * the input SAM definitions.

Create or refresh the tarball with:

     ./.tar.sh

Then submit a stage, for example:

     project.py --xml xml/numi_fhc_run1.xml --stage beam_shard0 --submit

For the staged XML, submit and check each stage before launching the next one.
Each later stage uses the checked output file list from the previous stage as
its default input:

     project.py --xml xml/numi_fhc_run1_staged.xml --stage beam_shard0_evtw --submit
     project.py --xml xml/numi_fhc_run1_staged.xml --stage beam_shard0_evtw --check
     project.py --xml xml/numi_fhc_run1_staged.xml --stage beam_shard0_image --submit
     project.py --xml xml/numi_fhc_run1_staged.xml --stage beam_shard0_image --check
     project.py --xml xml/numi_fhc_run1_staged.xml --stage beam_shard0_sel --submit

For the training XML, the same checked-output handoff applies, but there is no
inference stage.  If you point it at dedicated training SAM definitions, update
the XML input entities and `numjobs` counts to match those definitions.  Use
the MC-like stage families (`beam_*`, `dirt_*`, `strangeness_*`) for overlay
or truth-bearing training samples, and the `ext_*` stage families for data- or
EXT-like training samples:

     project.py --xml xml/numi_fhc_run1_training.xml --stage beam_shard0_evtw --submit
     project.py --xml xml/numi_fhc_run1_training.xml --stage beam_shard0_evtw --check
     project.py --xml xml/numi_fhc_run1_training.xml --stage beam_shard0_image --submit
     project.py --xml xml/numi_fhc_run1_training.xml --stage beam_shard0_image --check
     project.py --xml xml/numi_fhc_run1_training.xml --stage beam_shard0_sel --submit

For the stride-split detvar training XML, edit the two input SAM definitions
and `numjobs` values first, then run the image and selection stages:

     project.py --xml xml/numi_fhc_run1_detvar_training.xml --stage beam_detvar_nominal_train_image --submit
     project.py --xml xml/numi_fhc_run1_detvar_training.xml --stage beam_detvar_nominal_train_image --check
     project.py --xml xml/numi_fhc_run1_detvar_training.xml --stage beam_detvar_nominal_train_sel --submit

Checked-in stage names include:

  * beam_shard0
  * beam_shard1
  * beam_shard2
  * beam_shard3
  * beam_campaign_run2a_fhc
  * dirt_shard0
  * dirt_shard1
  * dirt_campaign_run2a_fhc
  * strangeness_campaign_run1_fhc
  * strangeness_campaign_run2a_fhc
  * ext_shard0
  * ext_shard1
  * ext_shard2
  * ext_campaign_run2a_p0
  * ext_campaign_run2a_p1
  * ext_campaign_run2a_p2
  * ext_campaign_run2a_p3

The Reco2 source-campaign XMLs use similarly named stage families such as:

  * beam_campaign_run1_fhc_sample0 through beam_campaign_run1_fhc_sample3
  * dirt_campaign_run1_fhc_sample0 and dirt_campaign_run1_fhc_sample1
  * strangeness_campaign_run1_fhc
  * ext_campaign_run1_fhc
  * data_campaign_run1_fhc
  * beam_campaign_run2a_fhc, dirt_campaign_run2a_fhc,
    strangeness_campaign_run2a_fhc, ext_campaign_run2a_fhc,
    data_campaign_run2a_fhc
  * beam_campaign_run2b_rhc, dirt_campaign_run2b_rhc,
    strangeness_campaign_run2b_rhc, ext_campaign_run2b_rhc,
    data_campaign_run2b_rhc
  * beam_campaign_run3b_rhc_sample0 through beam_campaign_run3b_rhc_sample3
  * dirt_campaign_run3b_rhc_sample0 and dirt_campaign_run3b_rhc_sample1
  * strangeness_campaign_run3b_rhc
  * ext_campaign_run3b_rhc
  * data_campaign_run3b_rhc

The staged XML uses dataset-specific stage chains such as:

  * beam_shard0_evtw, beam_shard0_image, beam_shard0_sel
  * beam_shard1_evtw, beam_shard1_image, beam_shard1_sel
  * beam_shard2_evtw, beam_shard2_image, beam_shard2_sel
  * beam_shard3_evtw, beam_shard3_image, beam_shard3_sel
  * dirt_shard0_evtw, dirt_shard0_image, dirt_shard0_sel
  * dirt_shard1_evtw, dirt_shard1_image, dirt_shard1_sel
  * strangeness_campaign_run1_fhc_evtw,
    strangeness_campaign_run1_fhc_image,
    strangeness_campaign_run1_fhc_sel
  * ext_shard0_image, ext_shard0_sel
  * ext_shard1_image, ext_shard1_sel
  * ext_shard2_image, ext_shard2_sel

The training XML uses the same sample stage names, but drops the infer stage:

  * beam_shard0_evtw, beam_shard0_image, beam_shard0_sel
  * beam_shard1_evtw, beam_shard1_image, beam_shard1_sel
  * beam_shard2_evtw, beam_shard2_image, beam_shard2_sel
  * beam_shard3_evtw, beam_shard3_image, beam_shard3_sel
  * dirt_shard0_evtw, dirt_shard0_image, dirt_shard0_sel
  * dirt_shard1_evtw, dirt_shard1_image, dirt_shard1_sel
  * strangeness_campaign_run1_fhc_evtw,
    strangeness_campaign_run1_fhc_image,
    strangeness_campaign_run1_fhc_sel
  * ext_shard0_image, ext_shard0_sel
  * ext_shard1_image, ext_shard1_sel
  * ext_shard2_image, ext_shard2_sel

The stride-split detvar training XML uses:

  * beam_detvar_nominal_train_image, beam_detvar_nominal_train_sel
  * strangeness_detvar_nominal_train_image, strangeness_detvar_nominal_train_sel

To clean and resubmit a stage:

     project.py --xml xml/numi_fhc_run1.xml --stage beam_shard0 --clean
     project.py --xml xml/numi_fhc_run1.xml --stage beam_shard0 --submit

For the staged XML, clean and resubmit the specific stage you want to rerun:

     project.py --xml xml/numi_fhc_run1_staged.xml --stage beam_shard0_image --clean
     project.py --xml xml/numi_fhc_run1_staged.xml --stage beam_shard0_image --submit


7. Common adjustments
---------------------

The checked-in job files are meant to be copied or overridden for your local
campaign.  Common edits include:

  * switching between MC and data by choosing the right top-level FHiCL file;
  * changing TFileService output names;
  * changing the inference model family, checkpoint, or wrapper path;
  * adjusting XML entities to point at your own PNFS areas and SAM inputs.

For development work, put ad hoc configurations under dev/ rather than editing
the production files in job/ without a reason.


8. If something fails early
---------------------------

Check the following first:

  * If lar cannot find included FHiCL files or products, your MRB setup is not
    complete.  Re-run source .setup.sh or the equivalent manual setup.
  * If samweb is missing, set up sam_web_client or use the helper setup script.
  * If an inference job fails immediately, confirm that you are running from
    the repository top directory and that
    runtime/models/mink_binary/checkpoint_step0010000.pt is present.
  * If a grid stage points to the wrong storage area, edit the entities in
    the XML file you are submitting before launching jobs.


End
